  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "At the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs), students enrolled in the BS-MS dual degree program typically receive a fellowship or stipend, but there are certain conditions and eligibility criteria. As of my last update, Indian students who are admitted through channels like KVPY, JEE, and SCB usually receive a fellowship provided by the Government of India, subject to the maintenance of a certain academic performance. This fellowship is intended to support students financially during their studies.\n\nFor PhD students, fellowships are also generally available, often funded by various government agencies or specific research projects. PhD fellowship eligibility might depend on factors such as passing national-level exams (e.g., CSIR-NET, GATE) or specific project requirements.\n\nHowever, policies can change, and it is important for students to check the latest updates on fellowship opportunities and eligibility directly from the official IISER website or contact the admissions office of the specific IISER campus they are interested in for the most accurate and current information.",
